          </div>
          <p>AOW recipients (people at or above state pension age throughout 2026) pay no AOW premium (17.90%), so their first bracket rate drops to {(nlB.b1RateAow * 100).toFixed(2)}%. Brackets 2 and 3 are unaffected. For people born before 1 January 1946, a slightly higher first-bracket ceiling may apply.</p>

          <h2 id="credits">Tax credits (heffingskortingen) 2026</h2>
          <p>Dutch tax credits reduce the income tax owed after applying the bracket rates. They are not deductions from income - they reduce the tax bill euro-for-euro. Both main credits phase out at higher incomes, so the net benefit decreases as your salary rises. Source: <a href="https://www.belastingdienst.nl/wps/wcm/connect/bldcontentnl/belastingdienst/prive/inkomstenbelasting/heffingskortingen_boxen_tarieven/heffingskortingen/algemene_heffingskorting/tabel-algemene-heffingskorting-2026" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Belastingdienst - Heffingskortingen 2026</a>.</p>
          <div class="responsive-table">
            <table>
