          </div>
          <p>The arbeidskorting builds up on a four-step scale before reaching its maximum. For incomes between €0 and €{nlA.s1Top.toLocaleString()}, the credit is {(nlA.s1Rate * 100).toFixed(3)}% of employment income. It rises steeply between €{nlA.s1Top.toLocaleString()} and €{nlA.s3Top.toLocaleString()}, reaching its peak at €{nlA.s4Base.toLocaleString()}, then phases down. This means low earners benefit proportionally more from this credit than middle earners.</p>

          <h2 id="step-by-step">Step-by-step: how to calculate Dutch net salary</h2>
          <p>The Dutch net salary calculation has four steps. For a €{ex.toLocaleString()} gross salary in 2026:</p>
